
Puck is a game for one or two players. 

Just type 'puck' to play.

For a two player game, the player on the faster machine
should type 'puck', after which the other player should
type 'puck name_of_other_machine'

Type 'puck -q' to play a quiet game with no audio effects.

-----

Note: puck uses sockets for communication, going through socket
ports 7777 and 7778 by default. If other processes on the machine
are already using one of those port numbers, you'll get a message:
"Cannot start game, sorry." If this happens, you'll need to tell puck
to use different port numbers. To do so, setenv PUCK_SOCKET_PORT
to some value until the game successfully starts (for instance,
'setenv PUCK_SOCKET_PORT 1800').
